article.description: Jalen Morgan scored 17 points on 6-of-7 shooting, and Western Illinois bounced back from its first loss of the season to top Silver Lake 84-49 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Western Illinois stays hot from 3, tops Silver Lake 84-49
article.linkText: Western Illinois stays hot from 3, tops Silver Lake 84-49
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Kobe Webster scored 21 points as Western Illinois easily defeated NAIA member Holy Family College 91-64 on Thursday night. Ben Pyle added 20 points for the Leathernecks. Zion Young had 16 points, six rebounds and six assists for Western Illinois (3-7). Jaeden King added 9 points. Thomas Bullock had 11 points for the Lakers. DeLoran Oliver added 10 points. Bryanth Farr had 14 rebounds to go with eight points. Western Illinois faces South Dakota at home next Sunday to open Summit League play. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
